node.text: When we take care of people, we take care of the planet. We’re donating 100M disease-resistant coffee trees by 2025 to help farmers and their communities, and committing to reduce our landfill waste by 50% by 2030.

node.title: Caring for Our Planet & Our People

node.text: Caramel forever. 😋 Caramel Ribbon Crunch Frappuccino® Drink

node.accessibility_caption: Two women wearing Starbucks green aprons. One holds a protein box and the other an orange FoodShare crate.

node.text:
100% of our U.S. company-owned stores are now donating food to local food banks. This program—called FoodShare—has helped provide nearly 34 million ready-to-eat meals in partnership with organizations like @feedingamerica.

And our work doesn’t stop there. We will continue to help our communities fight hunger because we believe that everyone should have access to nourishing food.

To learn more about the FoodShare program, check out our Instagram Story.

node.accessibility_caption: A hand holds a bag of Starbucks Reserve whole bean coffee with blossoms and bright morning sun  in the background.

node.text: Make your morning bright. Enjoy notes of orange blossom, milk chocolate, and a sweet caramel finish. Find @starbucksreserve Bolivia Sol de la Mañana at select US Starbucks stores.
